CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 19, 1955, pg. 1 reads: "Building Permit Granted - The Philip L. Harrises, extreme right, receive approval for a once denied building permit from We3st Mifflin Planning Commissioner, Emil Greenhaigh (second from left), at a Tuesday night meeting during which Atty. Richard F. Jones (fourth from right) argued that proposed plans for a four-lane highway through the borough which at present are mostly in minds of borough officials cannot constitute a legal basis for a denial of a building permit. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: West Mifflin Planning Commissioner, Emil Greenhaigh, second from left, granting building permit to Atty. Richard F. Jones, third from right, for Mr. and Mrs. Philip Harris, right, in West Mifflin borough office
